               <msContents>
                  <summary>F<locus target="#1r"/>-122r: Acts of Zena Marqos, ገድለ፡ አቡነ፡ ዜና፡ ማርቆስ፡, arranged by a later hand, in pen, for the days of the week.  F<locus target="#1r"/>-76v: Biography. F<locus target="#77r"/>-121r: Thirty-One Miracles of Zena Marqos.  F. ir: record of biography and gift: "The emperor was Menilek II; his servant was Qängazmač እባ ፍታው. His wife was ወለተ ማርያም. The town was እክሊል. He ordered a drum [as a gift] to the monastery. At that time the founder of the monastery was Abba ገብረ ማርያም. His brother was called ጥጋቤ, his [other] brother was Abba መተኮ, in the year of Mark [the Evangelist].  <locus target="#121r"/>: record of Will. In the time of Emperor Menilek, Abba ወልደ ኪሮስ, gives his inheritance to Abba ጥጋቤ. Names of judge and witnesses follow. The name of the scribe for the Will is ገብረ ማርያም, in the year of John [the Evangelist]. <locus target="#121v"/>-122r: Image of Zena Marqos</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
